f(x, y, z) = x + 5y + 2z
x^{2} + y^{2} + z^{2} = 1
\mathrm{(f(x,y,z))}^{2}
(1\cdot x + 5\cdot y + 2\cdot z)^2 \le (1^2 + 5^2 + 2^2)(x^2 + y^2 + z^2) = 30
\mathrm{f}_{max} = \mathrm{\sqrt30} = 5.477
\mathrm{f}_{min} = - 5.477.
